Day 20 â€“ Osintgram Tool

Osintgram = OSINT tool for Instagram analysis
Used to gather publicly available information from Instagram accounts.

Category:
OSINT (Open Source Intelligence)

Purpose:
- Collect publicly available profile data
- Analyze digital footprint
- Social media investigation (authorized use only)

What It Can Gather:
- Username information
- Followers & following list
- Hashtags used
- Tagged posts
- Captions & comments
- Publicly available contact info
- Profile picture download
- Stories (if public)

How It Works:
- Uses Instagram public data
- Automates information gathering
- Organizes data for analysis

Why It Is Important in Cybersecurity:
- Used in social engineering investigations
- Helps identify exposed personal information
- Useful in threat intelligence
- Helps understand digital footprint risks

Risks:
- Privacy invasion if misused
- Can be illegal without authorization
- Violates platform policies if abused

Defensive Awareness:
- Keep accounts private
- Limit personal information in bio
- Avoid sharing sensitive details
- Be careful with location tagging
- Review followers regularly

Key Concept:
OSINT does not hack accounts.
It collects publicly available data.

Important Reminder:
Ethical use only.
Never use for stalking, harassment, or unauthorized investigation.

Lesson Learned:
Social media can reveal more information than expected.
Digital footprint management is part of cybersecurity.
